  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Backpropagation Interactive Demonstration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    background: white;\n    color: black;\n    margin: 1em;\n  }\n  h1, h2 {\n    margin-top: 1em;\n    margin-bottom: 0.2em;\n  }\n  section {\n    margin-bottom: 1.5em;\n  }\n  input[type=\"number\"], input[type=\"text\"] {\n    width: 4em;\n  }\n  table {\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    margin-top: 0.2em;\n    margin-bottom: 1em;\n  }\n  th, td {\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n  button, input[type=\"range\"] {\n    margin-top: 0.3em;\n    margin-bottom: 0.3em;\n  }\n  textarea {\n    font-family: monospace;\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 6em;\n  }\n  label {\n    margin-right: 1em;\n  }\n  .controls-row {\n    margin-bottom: 0.5em;\n  }\n  .readonly-textarea {\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 10em;\n    font-family: monospace;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    overflow-wrap: break-word;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Backpropagation Interactive Demonstration</h1>\n\n<section id=\"intro\">\n  <p>This interactive demonstration shows how the <strong>Backpropagation</strong> algorithm works on a simple feedforward neural network for regression/classification.</p>\n  <p>You can create, configure, and train a simple network by controlling the architecture, inputs, outputs, and training steps. Explore the inner calculations step-by-step.</p>\n</section>\n\n<section id=\"network-setup\">\n  <h2>1. Network Architecture Setup</h2>\n  <div class=\"controls-row\">\n    <label for=\"input-nodes\">Input nodes:</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"input-nodes\" min=\"1\" max=\"10\" value=\"2\" />\n    <label for=\"hidden-nodes\">Hidden nodes:</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"hidden-nodes\" min=\"1\" max=\"10\" value=\"2\" />\n    <label for=\"output-nodes\">Output nodes:</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"output-nodes\" min=\"1\" max=\"4\" value=\"1\" />\n    <button id=\"build-network\">Build Network</button>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"network-state-note\"></div>\n</section>\n\n<section id=\"network-config\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>2. Network Weights and Biases</h2>\n  <p>Adjust initial weights and biases for each layer (input→hidden and hidden→output). Values from -2 to +2.</p>\n  <div id=\"weights-biases-controls\" style=\"overflow-x:auto; max-width:100%;\"></div>\n  <button id=\"reset-weights\">Reset All Weights & Biases</button>\n</section>\n\n<section id=\"training-inputs\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>3. Training Dataset</h2>\n  <p>Define training examples: input vector(s) and target output(s).</p>\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"training-input\">Input (comma separated numbers of length = input nodes):</label><br />\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"training-input\" placeholder=\"e.g. 0.5, -0.3\" style=\"width: 25em;\" />\n  </div>\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"training-target\">Target output (comma separated numbers of length = output nodes):</label><br />\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"training-target\" placeholder=\"e.g. 1\" style=\"width: 15em;\" />\n  </div>\n  <button id=\"add-training-example\">Add Training Example</button>\n  <button id=\"clear-training-examples\">Clear Training Examples</button>\n  <h3>Training Examples:</h3>\n  <div id=\"training-examples-list\" style=\"max-height:9em; overflow-y:auto; border:1px solid black; padding:0.3em;\">\n    <em>No training examples added.</em>\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<section id=\"training-controls\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>4. Training Controls</h2>\n  <div class=\"controls-row\">\n    <label for=\"learning-rate\">Learning rate (η):</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"learning-rate\" min=\"0.0001\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.0001\" value=\"0.1\" />\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"controls-row\">\n    <label for=\"max-epochs\">Epochs to train:</label>\n    <input type=\"number\" id=\"max-epochs\" min=\"1\" max=\"10000\" value=\"100\" />\n  </div>\n  <button id=\"train-step\">Train One Epoch</button>\n  <button id=\"train-many\">Train Multiple Epochs</button>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"train-many-count\" min=\"1\" max=\"1000\" value=\"10\" style=\"width:5em;\" />\n  <button id=\"reset-network\">Reset Network Weights/Biases</button>\n</section>\n\n<section id=\"example-forward\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>5. Forward Pass / Prediction</h2>\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"forward-input\">Input vector (comma separated):</label><br />\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"forward-input\" style=\"width: 25em;\" />\n  </div>\n  <button id=\"run-forward\">Run Forward Pass</button>\n  <button id=\"show-layer-outputs\">Show Layer Outputs</button>\n  <pre id=\"forward-output\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; border:1px solid black; padding:0.5em; min-height:4em;\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<section id=\"backprop-steps\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>6. Step-by-step Backpropagation</h2>\n  <p>Explore the computed gradients and weight updates per layer in a detailed stepwise manner.</p>\n  <div>\n    <button id=\"start-bp-step\">Start Backpropagation Step-Through</button>\n    <button id=\"next-bp-step\" disabled>Next Step</button>\n    <button id=\"prev-bp-step\" disabled>Previous Step</button>\n    <button id=\"cancel-bp-step\" disabled>Cancel Step-Through</button>\n  </div>\n  <pre id=\"bp-step-output\" style=\"border:1px solid black; padding:0.5em; min-height:6em; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<section>\n  <h2>7. Internal State Summary</h2>\n  <button id=\"show-state\">Show Current Network State</button>\n  <pre id=\"network-state\" class=\"readonly-textarea\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // State definitions and helpers\n  let network = null;\n  // network structure:\n  // {\n  //   inputCount: number,\n  //   hiddenCount: number,\n  //   outputCount: number,\n  //   weightsIH: array of arrays [hiddenCount][inputCount] floats,\n  //   weightsHO: array of arrays [outputCount][hiddenCount] floats,\n  //   biasesH: array [hiddenCount] floats,\n  //   biasesO: array [outputCount] floats,\n  //   activationH: array [hiddenCount] floats (last activation after forward),\n  //   activationO: array [outputCount] floats (last activation after forward),\n  // }\n  // trainingData: [{input:[], target:[]}]\n\n  let trainingData = [];\n\n  // Backprop stepper state:\n  const BackpropSteps = [\n    \"Calculate output layer errors\",\n    \"Calculate output layer gradients (derivatives * error * learning rate)\",\n    \"Calculate hidden layer errors\",\n    \"Calculate hidden layer gradients\",\n    \"Update weights hidden→output\",\n    \"Update biases output layer\",\n    \"Update weights input→hidden\",\n    \"Update biases hidden layer\",\n    \"Completed\"\n  ];\n  let bpStepIndex = -1;\n  let bpRunning = false;\n  let bpLastForward = null;\n  let bpLastErrors = null;\n  let bpLastGradients = null;\n  let bpLastLearningRate = 0;\n\n  function sigmoid(x) { return 1 / (1 + Math.exp(-x)); }\n  function sigmoidDerivative(y) { return y * (1 - y); } // y = sigmoid(x)\n  function randomWeight() {\n    return (Math.random() - 0.5) * 4; // -2 to 2 random float\n  }\n\n  // Utilities\n  function arrayFill(len, val=0){ return Array.from({length: len}, () => val); }\n\n  // Build network on demand\n  function buildNetwork(inputCount, hiddenCount, outputCount) {\n    const weightsIH = [];\n    for(let h=0;h<hiddenCount;h++){\n      weightsIH[h] = [];\n      for(let i=0;i<inputCount;i++){\n        weightsIH[h][i] = randomWeight();\n      }\n    }\n    const weightsHO = [];\n    for(let o=0;o<outputCount;o++){\n      weightsHO[o] = [];\n      for(let h=0;h<hiddenCount;h++){\n        weightsHO[o][h] = randomWeight();\n      }\n    }\n    const biasesH = arrayFill(hiddenCount).map(() => randomWeight());\n    const biasesO = arrayFill(outputCount).map(() => randomWeight());\n    return {\n      inputCount,\n      hiddenCount,\n      outputCount,\n      weightsIH,\n      weightsHO,\n      biasesH,\n      biasesO,\n      activationH: arrayFill(hiddenCount, 0),\n      activationO: arrayFill(outputCount, 0),\n    };\n  }\n\n  function validateArchitectureInput(){\n    const i = parseInt(inputNodesInput.value, 10);\n    const h = parseInt(hiddenNodesInput.value, 10);\n    const o = parseInt(outputNodesInput.value, 10);\n    if(isNaN(i) || i<1 || i>10) return false;\n    if(isNaN(h) || h<1 || h>10) return false;\n    if(isNaN(o) || o<1 || o>4) return false;\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Render the weights and biases controls dynamically\n  function renderWeightsBiasesControls(){\n    const container = weightsBiasesControlsDiv;\n    container.innerHTML = '';\n\n    if(!network) return;\n\n    // Table for input->hidden weights\n    let html = '<h3>Input → Hidden weights and biases</h3>';\n    html += '<table><thead><tr><th>Hidden node \\\\ Input node</th>';\n    for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n      html += '<th>i'+i+'</th>';\n    }\n    html += '</tr></thead><tbody>';\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      html += `<tr><th>h${h}</th>`;\n      for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n        const w = network.weightsIH[h][i].toFixed(3);\n        html += `<td><input type=\"number\" step=\"0.001\" min=\"-5\" max=\"5\" data-layer=\"IH\" data-h=\"${h}\" data-i=\"${i}\" value=\"${w}\"></td>`;\n      }\n      html += `<td>Bias: <input type=\"number\" step=\"0.001\" min=\"-5\" max=\"5\" data-layer=\"bH\" data-h=\"${h}\" value=\"${network.biasesH[h].toFixed(3)}\"></td>`;\n      html += '</tr>';\n    }\n    html += '</tbody></table>';\n\n    // Table for hidden->output weights\n    html += '<h3>Hidden → Output weights and biases</h3>';\n    html += '<table><thead><tr><th>Output node \\\\ Hidden node</th>';\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      html += '<th>h'+h+'</th>';\n    }\n    html += '</tr></thead><tbody>';\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      html += `<tr><th>o${o}</th>`;\n      for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n        const w = network.weightsHO[o][h].toFixed(3);\n        html += `<td><input type=\"number\" step=\"0.001\" min=\"-5\" max=\"5\" data-layer=\"HO\" data-o=\"${o}\" data-h=\"${h}\" value=\"${w}\"></td>`;\n      }\n      html += `<td>Bias: <input type=\"number\" step=\"0.001\" min=\"-5\" max=\"5\" data-layer=\"bO\" data-o=\"${o}\" value=\"${network.biasesO[o].toFixed(3)}\"></td>`;\n      html += '</tr>';\n    }\n    html += '</tbody></table>';\n\n    container.innerHTML = html;\n\n    // Add event listeners to inputs to update network state as user changes values\n    const inputs = container.querySelectorAll('input[type=\"number\"]');\n    inputs.forEach(input => {\n      input.addEventListener('change', (e) => {\n        const target = e.target;\n        const layer = target.dataset.layer;\n        if(layer === 'IH'){\n          const h = parseInt(target.dataset.h, 10);\n          const i = parseInt(target.dataset.i, 10);\n          let v = parseFloat(target.value);\n          if(isNaN(v)) v = 0;\n          network.weightsIH[h][i] = v;\n        } else if(layer === 'HO'){\n          const o = parseInt(target.dataset.o, 10);\n          const h = parseInt(target.dataset.h, 10);\n          let v = parseFloat(target.value);\n          if(isNaN(v)) v = 0;\n          network.weightsHO[o][h] = v;\n        } else if(layer === 'bH'){\n          const h = parseInt(target.dataset.h, 10);\n          let v = parseFloat(target.value);\n          if(isNaN(v)) v = 0;\n          network.biasesH[h] = v;\n        } else if(layer === 'bO'){\n          const o = parseInt(target.dataset.o, 10);\n          let v = parseFloat(target.value);\n          if(isNaN(v)) v = 0;\n          network.biasesO[o] = v;\n        }\n      });\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Network forward pass returns output activations and stores hidden activations in network state\n  function forwardPass(inputArray){\n    if(!network) return null;\n    if(!Array.isArray(inputArray) || inputArray.length !== network.inputCount) return null;\n\n    // Hidden layer calculation: sum weights*inputs + bias, then sigmoid\n    let hiddenActivations = [];\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      let sum = network.biasesH[h];\n      for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n        sum += network.weightsIH[h][i] * inputArray[i];\n      }\n      hiddenActivations[h] = sigmoid(sum);\n    }\n    network.activationH = hiddenActivations;\n\n    // Output layer calculation: sum weights*hidden + bias, then sigmoid\n    let outputActivations = [];\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      let sum = network.biasesO[o];\n      for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n        sum += network.weightsHO[o][h] * hiddenActivations[h];\n      }\n      outputActivations[o] = sigmoid(sum);\n    }\n    network.activationO = outputActivations;\n\n    return outputActivations;\n  }\n\n  // Training step: run backpropagation for one training example, update weights and biases\n  function backpropagate(inputArr, targetArr, learningRate){\n    if(!network) return false;\n\n    // Forward pass\n    const outputs = forwardPass(inputArr);\n\n    // Output errors: target - outputs\n    let outputErrors = [];\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      outputErrors[o] = targetArr[o] - outputs[o];\n    }\n\n    // Calculate output gradients: derivative * error * learning rate\n    let outputGradients = [];\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      const derivative = sigmoidDerivative(outputs[o]);\n      outputGradients[o] = derivative * outputErrors[o] * learningRate;\n    }\n\n    // Calculate hidden errors by weightsHO weighted sums of output gradients\n    let hiddenErrors = [];\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      let sum = 0;\n      for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n        sum += network.weightsHO[o][h] * outputGradients[o];\n      }\n      hiddenErrors[h] = sum;\n    }\n\n    // Calculate hidden gradients: derivative * error * learning rate\n    let hiddenGradients = [];\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      const derivative = sigmoidDerivative(network.activationH[h]);\n      hiddenGradients[h] = derivative * hiddenErrors[h]; // Note learningRate included in outputGradients only to keep the chain clear here\n    }\n\n    // Update weights hidden→output\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n        network.weightsHO[o][h] += outputGradients[o] * network.activationH[h];\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Update biases output\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      network.biasesO[o] += outputGradients[o];\n    }\n\n    // Update weights input→hidden\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n        network.weightsIH[h][i] += hiddenGradients[h] * inputArr[i] * learningRate;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Update biases hidden\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      network.biasesH[h] += hiddenGradients[h] * learningRate;\n    }\n\n    return {\n      outputErrors,\n      outputGradients,\n      hiddenErrors,\n      hiddenGradients,\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Clear training data UI and internal\n  function clearTrainingData(){\n    trainingData = [];\n    trainingExamplesListDiv.innerHTML = '<em>No training examples added.</em>';\n  }\n\n  // Add training example from UI inputs\n  function addTrainingExample(){\n    const inputTxt = trainingInputText.value.trim();\n    const targetTxt = trainingTargetText.value.trim();\n    if(inputTxt.length===0 || targetTxt.length===0){\n      alert(\"Both input and target are required.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const inputParts = inputTxt.split(',').map(x=>x.trim()).filter(x=>x.length>0);\n    if(inputParts.length !== network.inputCount){\n      alert(`Input length mismatch: expected ${network.inputCount}, got ${inputParts.length}`);\n      return;\n    }\n    const targetParts = targetTxt.split(',').map(x=>x.trim()).filter(x=>x.length>0);\n    if(targetParts.length !== network.outputCount){\n      alert(`Target length mismatch: expected ${network.outputCount}, got ${targetParts.length}`);\n      return;\n    }\n    const inputs = [];\n    for(let i=0;i<inputParts.length;i++){\n      const v = parseFloat(inputParts[i]);\n      if(isNaN(v)){\n        alert(\"Invalid number in input.\");\n        return;\n      }\n      inputs.push(v);\n    }\n    const targets = [];\n    for(let i=0;i<targetParts.length;i++){\n      const v = parseFloat(targetParts[i]);\n      if(isNaN(v)){\n        alert(\"Invalid number in target.\");\n        return;\n      }\n      targets.push(v);\n    }\n    trainingData.push({input: inputs, target: targets});\n    renderTrainingData();\n    trainingInputText.value = '';\n    trainingTargetText.value = '';\n  }\n\n  // Render training data list\n  function renderTrainingData(){\n    if(trainingData.length === 0){\n      trainingExamplesListDiv.innerHTML = '<em>No training examples added.</em>';\n      return;\n    }\n    let html = '<ol>';\n    for(let i=0;i<trainingData.length;i++){\n      const ex = trainingData[i];\n      html += `<li>Input: [${ex.input.map(v=>v.toFixed(3)).join(', ')}], Target: [${ex.target.map(v=>v.toFixed(3)).join(', ')}]\n      <button data-index=\"${i}\" class=\"remove-training-example\">Remove</button></li>`;\n    }\n    html += '</ol>';\n    trainingExamplesListDiv.innerHTML = html;\n    // Add remove buttons listeners\n    const buttons = trainingExamplesListDiv.querySelectorAll('button.remove-training-example');\n    buttons.forEach(b => {\n      b.onclick = (e) => {\n        const idx = parseInt(e.target.dataset.index, 10);\n        trainingData.splice(idx, 1);\n        renderTrainingData();\n      };\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Run training on all training data once\n  function trainOneEpoch(){\n    if(!network) return;\n    if(trainingData.length === 0){\n      alert(\"No training data to train on.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const lr = parseFloat(learningRateInput.value);\n    if(isNaN(lr) || lr<=0){\n      alert(\"Invalid learning rate.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    let totalLoss = 0;\n    for(let ex of trainingData){\n      const bpStats = backpropagate(ex.input, ex.target, lr);\n      // sum squared error loss outputErrors^2 /2\n      for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n        const err = bpStats.outputErrors[o];\n        totalLoss += err*err/2;\n      }\n    }\n    return totalLoss/trainingData.length;\n  }\n\n  // Train many epochs on demand\n  function trainMultipleEpochs(count) {\n    if(!network) return;\n    if(trainingData.length === 0){\n      alert(\"No training data to train on.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const lr = parseFloat(learningRateInput.value);\n    if(isNaN(lr) || lr<=0){\n      alert(\"Invalid learning rate.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    let avgLoss = 0;\n    for(let e=0;e<count;e++){\n      avgLoss = trainOneEpoch();\n    }\n    return avgLoss;\n  }\n\n  // Reset weights and biases to random\n  function resetWeightsBiases(){\n    if(!network) return;\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n        network.weightsIH[h][i] = randomWeight();\n      }\n      network.biasesH[h] = randomWeight();\n    }\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n        network.weightsHO[o][h] = randomWeight();\n      }\n      network.biasesO[o] = randomWeight();\n    }\n    renderWeightsBiasesControls();\n  }\n\n  // Parse CSV input vector\n  function parseCsvVector(text, expectedLen){\n    const parts = text.split(',').map(x=>x.trim()).filter(x=>x.length>0);\n    if(parts.length !== expectedLen) return null;\n    let vals = [];\n    for(let i=0;i<parts.length;i++){\n      let v = parseFloat(parts[i]);\n      if(isNaN(v)) return null;\n      vals.push(v);\n    }\n    return vals;\n  }\n\n  // Show layer activations for last forward pass\n  function showLayerOutputs(){\n    if(!network) {\n      forwardOutputPre.textContent = 'No network.';\n      return;\n    }\n    const hAct = network.activationH.map(v=>v.toFixed(6));\n    const oAct = network.activationO.map(v=>v.toFixed(6));\n    let text = 'Hidden layer activations:\\n';\n    for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n      text += `h${h}: ${hAct[h]}\\n`;\n    }\n    text += '\\nOutput layer activations:\\n';\n    for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n      text += `o${o}: ${oAct[o]}\\n`;\n    }\n    forwardOutputPre.textContent = text;\n  }\n\n  // Show forward pass output\n  function runForwardForInput(){\n    if(!network) return;\n    let inputVec = parseCsvVector(forwardInputText.value, network.inputCount);\n    if(!inputVec){\n      forwardOutputPre.textContent = 'Invalid input vector.';\n      return;\n    }\n    let out = forwardPass(inputVec);\n    if(!out){\n      forwardOutputPre.textContent = 'Failed to compute output.';\n      return;\n    }\n    let text = 'Output:\\n[' + out.map(v=>v.toFixed(6)).join(', ') + ']';\n    forwardOutputPre.textContent = text;\n  }\n\n  // Show current network state as JSON text\n  function showNetworkState(){\n    if(!network){\n      networkStatePre.textContent = 'No network built.';\n      return;\n    }\n    // For clarity avoid circular refs and large data, only show arrays of weights, biases, counts\n    const state = {\n      inputCount: network.inputCount,\n      hiddenCount: network.hiddenCount,\n      outputCount: network.outputCount,\n      weightsIH: network.weightsIH,\n      weightsHO: network.weightsHO,\n      biasesH: network.biasesH,\n      biasesO: network.biasesO,\n    };\n    networkStatePre.textContent = JSON.stringify(state, null, 2);\n  }\n\n  // Backpropagate detailed stepwise logic for one example\n  let bpStepData = null;\n  function startBackpropStep(){\n    if(!network) return false;\n    if(trainingData.length === 0){\n      alert(\"Add training data to explore backpropagation steps.\");\n      return false;\n    }\n    // Pick first training example for step-through demo\n    const ex = trainingData[0];\n    bpStepData = {};\n    bpStepData.input = ex.input;\n    bpStepData.target = ex.target;\n    bpStepData.learningRate = parseFloat(learningRateInput.value);\n    if(isNaN(bpStepData.learningRate) || bpStepData.learningRate <= 0){\n      alert(\"Invalid learning rate.\");\n      return false;\n    }\n    // forward pass\n    const outputActivations = forwardPass(bpStepData.input);\n    bpStepData.activationH = network.activationH.slice();\n    bpStepData.activationO = network.activationO.slice();\n\n    // Stepwise info initialized\n    bpStepData.outputErrors = null;\n    bpStepData.outputGradients = null;\n    bpStepData.hiddenErrors = null;\n    bpStepData.hiddenGradients = null;\n    bpStepData.weightsHO_before = network.weightsHO.map(row => row.slice());\n    bpStepData.biasesO_before = network.biasesO.slice();\n    bpStepData.weightsIH_before = network.weightsIH.map(row => row.slice());\n    bpStepData.biasesH_before = network.biasesH.slice();\n\n    bpStepIndex = 0;\n    bpRunning = true;\n    nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n    prevBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n    cancelBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n    startBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n    updateBpStepOutput();\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  function cancelBackpropStep(){\n    bpStepIndex = -1;\n    bpStepData = null;\n    bpRunning = false;\n    bpStepOutputPre.textContent = '';\n    nextBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n    prevBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n    cancelBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n    startBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n  }\n\n  function updateBpStepOutput(){\n    if(!bpRunning || !bpStepData) {\n      bpStepOutputPre.textContent = '';\n      return;\n    }\n    const stepDesc = BackpropSteps[bpStepIndex];\n    let txt = `Step ${bpStepIndex+1}: ${stepDesc}\\n\\n`;\n    const rate = bpStepData.learningRate;\n    switch(bpStepIndex){\n      case 0:\n        // Calculate output layer errors: target - outputActivations\n        bpStepData.outputErrors = [];\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          bpStepData.outputErrors[o] = bpStepData.target[o] - bpStepData.activationO[o];\n        }\n        txt += 'Output Errors (target - output):\\n';\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          txt += `o${o}: ${bpStepData.target[o].toFixed(6)} - ${bpStepData.activationO[o].toFixed(6)} = ${bpStepData.outputErrors[o].toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n        }\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 1:\n        // Calculate output gradients: derivative* error * learning rate\n        bpStepData.outputGradients = [];\n        txt += 'Output Gradients: sigmoid\\'(output) * error * learning rate\\n';\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          const d = sigmoidDerivative(bpStepData.activationO[o]);\n          bpStepData.outputGradients[o] = d * bpStepData.outputErrors[o] * rate;\n          txt += `o${o}: derivative=${d.toFixed(6)} * error=${bpStepData.outputErrors[o].toFixed(6)} * lr=${rate} = ${bpStepData.outputGradients[o].toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n        }\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 2:\n        // Hidden errors: sum weightsHO * output gradients per hidden node\n        bpStepData.hiddenErrors = [];\n        txt += 'Hidden Errors: sum over output nodes of (weightsHO * outputGradients)\\n';\n        for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n          let sum = 0;\n          for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n            sum += bpStepData.weightsHO_before[o][h] * bpStepData.outputGradients[o];\n          }\n          bpStepData.hiddenErrors[h] = sum;\n          txt += `h${h}: `;\n          for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n            txt += `wHO[${o}][${h}]=${bpStepData.weightsHO_before[o][h].toFixed(6)} * grad=${bpStepData.outputGradients[o].toFixed(6)}`;\n            if(o<network.outputCount-1) txt += \" + \";\n          }\n          txt += `= ${sum.toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n        }\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 3:\n        // Hidden gradients: derivative * hiddenErrors (learning rate applied later)\n        bpStepData.hiddenGradients = [];\n        txt += \"Hidden Gradients: sigmoid'(hidden activation) * hidden errors\\n\";\n        for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n          const d = sigmoidDerivative(bpStepData.activationH[h]);\n          const grad = d * bpStepData.hiddenErrors[h];\n          bpStepData.hiddenGradients[h] = grad;\n          txt += `h${h}: derivative=${d.toFixed(6)} * hiddenError=${bpStepData.hiddenErrors[h].toFixed(6)} = ${grad.toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n        }\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 4:\n        // Update weights hidden->output: weightsHO[o][h] += outputGradients[o] * activationH[h]\n        txt += \"Updating weights hidden→output:\\n\";\n        const wgHO = bpStepData.weightsHO_before.map(row => row.slice());\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n            const delta = bpStepData.outputGradients[o] * bpStepData.activationH[h];\n            const old = wgHO[o][h];\n            wgHO[o][h] = old + delta;\n            txt += `wHO[${o}][${h}]: ${old.toFixed(6)} + ${delta.toFixed(6)} = ${wgHO[o][h].toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n          }\n        }\n        // Show updated weightsHO after this step (simulate only)\n        txt += \"\\n(These updates will be committed at step 7)\\n\";\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 5:\n        // Update biases output: biasesO[o] += outputGradients[o]\n        txt += \"Updating biases output layer:\\n\";\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          const old = bpStepData.biasesO_before[o];\n          const delta = bpStepData.outputGradients[o];\n          const updated = old + delta;\n          txt += `bO[${o}]: ${old.toFixed(6)} + ${delta.toFixed(6)} = ${updated.toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n        }\n        txt += \"\\n(These updates will be committed at step 7)\\n\";\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 6:\n        // Update weights input→hidden: weightsIH[h][i] += hiddenGradients[h] * input[i] * learningRate\n        txt += \"Updating weights input→hidden:\\n\";\n        const wgIH = bpStepData.weightsIH_before.map(row => row.slice());\n        for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n          for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n            const delta = bpStepData.hiddenGradients[h] * bpStepData.input[i] * bpStepData.learningRate;\n            const old = wgIH[h][i];\n            wgIH[h][i] = old + delta;\n            txt += `wIH[${h}][${i}]: ${old.toFixed(6)} + ${delta.toFixed(6)} = ${wgIH[h][i].toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n          }\n        }\n        txt += \"\\n(These updates will be committed at step 8)\\n\";\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 7:\n        // Update biases hidden layer: biasesH[h] += hiddenGradients[h] * learningRate\n        txt += \"Updating biases hidden layer:\\n\";\n        for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n          const old = bpStepData.biasesH_before[h];\n          const delta = bpStepData.hiddenGradients[h] * bpStepData.learningRate;\n          const updated = old + delta;\n          txt += `bH[${h}]: ${old.toFixed(6)} + ${delta.toFixed(6)} = ${updated.toFixed(6)}\\n`;\n        }\n        txt += \"\\nFinally committing all weight and bias updates to network state.\\n\";\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n      case 8:\n        // Completed: commit updates to network state\n        // Apply all updates now to the actual network weights and biases:\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n            network.weightsHO[o][h] += bpStepData.outputGradients[o] * bpStepData.activationH[h];\n          }\n        }\n        for(let o=0;o<network.outputCount;o++){\n          network.biasesO[o] += bpStepData.outputGradients[o];\n        }\n        for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n          for(let i=0;i<network.inputCount;i++){\n            network.weightsIH[h][i] += bpStepData.hiddenGradients[h] * bpStepData.input[i] * bpStepData.learningRate;\n          }\n        }\n        for(let h=0;h<network.hiddenCount;h++){\n          network.biasesH[h] += bpStepData.hiddenGradients[h] * bpStepData.learningRate;\n        }\n        txt += \"Backpropagation step is complete and weights and biases updated.\\n\";\n        nextBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n        prevBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n        break;\n    }\n    bpStepOutputPre.textContent = txt;\n    renderWeightsBiasesControls(); // keep controls synced with network state\n  }\n\n  function nextBpStep(){\n    if(!bpRunning) return;\n    if(bpStepIndex+1 >= BackpropSteps.length) return;\n    bpStepIndex++;\n    updateBpStepOutput();\n    prevBpStepBtn.disabled = (bpStepIndex === 0);\n    if(bpStepIndex === BackpropSteps.length-1){\n      nextBpStepBtn.disabled = true;\n    } else {\n      nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  function prevBpStep(){\n    if(!bpRunning) return;\n    if(bpStepIndex <=0) return;\n    bpStepIndex--;\n    updateBpStepOutput();\n    prevBpStepBtn.disabled = (bpStepIndex === 0);\n    nextBpStepBtn.disabled = false;\n  }\n\n  // UI elements refs\n  const inputNodesInput = document.getElementById('input-nodes');\n  const hiddenNodesInput = document.getElementById('hidden-nodes');\n  const outputNodesInput = document.getElementById('output-nodes');\n  const buildNetworkBtn = document.getElementById('build-network');\n  const networkStateNoteDiv = document.getElementById('network-state-note');\n\n  const weightsBiasesControlsDiv = document.getElementById('weights-biases-controls');\n  const resetWeightsBtn = document.getElementById('reset-weights');\n\n  const trainingInputText = document.getElementById('training-input');\n  const trainingTargetText = document.getElementById('training-target');\n  const addTrainingExampleBtn = document.getElementById('add-training-example');\n  const clearTrainingExamplesBtn = document.getElementById('clear-training-examples');\n  const trainingExamplesListDiv = document.getElementById('training-examples-list');\n\n  const learningRateInput = document.getElementById('learning-rate');\n  const maxEpochsInput = document.getElementById('max-epochs');\n  const trainStepBtn = document.getElementById('train-step');\n  const trainManyBtn = document.getElementById('train-many');\n  const trainManyCountInput = document.getElementById('train-many-count');\n  const resetNetworkBtn = document.getElementById('reset-network');\n\n  const forwardInputText = document.getElementById('forward-input');\n  const runForwardBtn = document.getElementById('run-forward');\n  const showLayerOutputsBtn = document.getElementById('show-layer-outputs');\n  const forwardOutputPre = document.getElementById('forward-output');\n\n  const startBpStepBtn = document.getElementById('start-bp-step');\n  const nextBpStepBtn = document.getElementById('next-bp-step');\n  const prevBpStepBtn = document.getElementById('prev-bp-step');\n  const cancelBpStepBtn = document.getElementById('cancel-bp-step');\n  const bpStepOutputPre = document.getElementById('bp-step-output');\n\n  const showStateBtn = document.getElementById('show-state');\n  const networkStatePre = document.getElementById('network-state');\n\n  const networkConfigSec = document.getElementById('network-config');\n  const trainingInputsSec = document.getElementById('training-inputs');\n  const trainingControlsSec = document.getElementById('training-controls');\n  const exampleForwardSec = document.getElementById('example-forward');\n  const backpropStepsSec = document.getElementById('backprop-steps');\n\n  // Event Handlers\n\n  buildNetworkBtn.onclick = () => {\n    if(!validateArchitectureInput()){\n      alert(\"Invalid architecture inputs. Input nodes: 1-10, hidden nodes: 1-10, output nodes:1-4.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const i = parseInt(inputNodesInput.value,10);\n    const h = parseInt(hiddenNodesInput.value,10);\n    const o = parseInt(outputNodesInput.value,10);\n    network = buildNetwork(i,h,o);\n    networkStateNoteDiv.textContent = `Network built: ${i} inputs → ${h} hidden → ${o} outputs`;\n    renderWeightsBiasesControls();\n\n    // Show further sections\n    networkConfigSec.style.display = '';\n    trainingInputsSec.style.display = '';\n    trainingControlsSec.style.display = '';\n    exampleForwardSec.style.display = '';\n    backpropStepsSec.style.display = '';\n\n    // Clear training data\n    clearTrainingData();\n\n    // Reset outputs\n    forwardOutputPre.textContent = '';\n    bpStepOutputPre.textContent = '';\n    networkStatePre.textContent = '';\n\n    // Reset forward input box\n    let defaultInput = [];\n    for(let x=0; x<i; x++) defaultInput.push(0);\n    forwardInputText.value = defaultInput.join(', ');\n  };\n\n  resetWeightsBtn.onclick = () => {\n    if(!network) return;\n    resetWeightsBiases();\n  };\n\n  addTrainingExampleBtn.onclick = () => addTrainingExample();\n  clearTrainingExamplesBtn.onclick = () => clearTrainingData();\n\n  trainStepBtn.onclick = () => {\n    if(!network) return;\n    if(trainingData.length === 0){\n      alert(\"Add some training data first.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const loss = trainOneEpoch();\n    alert(`Trained 1 epoch on all examples.\\nAverage loss: ${loss.toFixed(6)}`);\n  };\n  trainManyBtn.onclick = () => {\n    if(!network) return;\n    if(trainingData.length === 0){\n      alert(\"Add some training data first.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    let count = parseInt(trainManyCountInput.value,10);\n    if(isNaN(count) || count < 1) {\n      alert(\"Invalid number of epochs to train.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const loss = trainMultipleEpochs(count);\n    alert(`Trained ${count} epochs on all examples.\\nAverage loss: ${loss.toFixed(6)}`);\n  };\n  resetNetworkBtn.onclick = () => {\n    if(!network) return;\n    resetWeightsBiases();\n  };\n\n  runForwardBtn.onclick = () => {\n    runForwardForInput();\n  };\n\n  showLayerOutputsBtn.onclick = () => {\n    showLayerOutputs();\n  };\n\n  showStateBtn.onclick = () => {\n    showNetworkState();\n  };\n\n  startBpStepBtn.onclick = () => {\n    const ok = startBackpropStep();\n    if(!ok) return;\n  };\n  nextBpStepBtn.onclick = () => nextBpStep();\n  prevBpStepBtn.onclick = () => prevBpStep();\n  cancelBpStepBtn.onclick = () => cancelBackpropStep();\n\n  // Initialize disabled states except build:\n  networkConfigSec.style.display = 'none';\n  trainingInputsSec.style.display = 'none';\n  trainingControlsSec.style.display = 'none';\n  exampleForwardSec.style.display = 'none';\n  backpropStepsSec.style.display = 'none';\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
